session-appended 2026-05-20 expl-demo follow-up #5 (HEAD 7bae597 session-0016 re-anchor). Diff vs session-0015 introduces `ScanTriggerSource { Manual | Scheduler{label} | Webhook }` (state.rs:27-57), routes Manual through `scan_project` (router.rs:1141), Webhook through `webhook_git` (webhook.rs:598), and Scheduler through `Scheduler::tick` (scheduler.rs:166). Source is stamped into `runs.triggered_by` via `as_run_record_string()` — Manual→"UI", Webhook→"Webhook", Scheduler→`format!("Cron:{label}")`. Also adds `findings.spec_id` plumbing (store/finding.rs:170, exposed on every read path) and the PATCH-side `validate_git_auth_ref` re-validation (router.rs:830-836, validator at :867-887). All 15 prior findings still pin; only validate_git_auth_ref shifted from :864 to :867 (+3 lines). Webhook handler / HMAC / replay-bundle path / extract_ustar all unchanged. No new findings emitted this round — the new attack surfaces re-traced:

(a) **ScanTriggerSource label flow** (scheduler.rs:166 → state.rs:51 → runs.triggered_by → run_card.rs:381). `entry.label` flows from `ConfigSchedule.label` (operator-config TOML, trusted). `render_markdown` wraps via `markdown_code()` (run_card.rs:381) so backtick-escaped; `render_html` wraps via `escape_html()` (:299). No injection sink reachable from a tenant-controllable source. Benign.

(b) **PATCH `validate_git_auth_ref` regression** (router.rs:830-836). The PATCH path now re-validates every call with `effective_source_kind` + `effective_auth_ref`, even when neither field is in the request payload. A repo row created *before* session-0014 with a malformed `auth_ref` and `source_kind ∈ {git, github, gitlab}` will reject every later PATCH (e.g. updating `branch` or `enabled`) with 400 until the operator explicitly clears `auth_ref` via `Some(None)`. This is a backward-compat *availability* regression, not a vuln-class; not emitted as a finding. Mitigation worth noting: only re-validate when `req.auth_ref` or `req.source_kind` is present in the payload.

(c) **Validator local-path bypass** (router.rs:870-872). `validate_git_auth_ref` returns Ok early when `source_kind` ∉ {git, github, gitlab}. Create-then-PATCH walks the lattice: CREATE with `source_kind=local-path` + arbitrary `auth_ref` succeeds (no validation), then PATCH with `source_kind=git` re-validates and rejects if the carried-over value is malformed. So the bypass *does* close on transition to a git-family kind. Findings #13 (ssh-key shell-injection via GIT_SSH_COMMAND) and #14 (token-env arbitrary-env exfil) remain primary primitives because they exploit the *grammar-conforming* shapes the validator accepts, not the bypass.

(d) **`GET /api/v1/chains?run_id=…` unbounded read** (router.rs:1313-1322, chain.rs:79-104). `list_by_run` issues a `SELECT … FROM chains WHERE run_id = ?` with no LIMIT and materialises the full result set including `rationale_blob` + `member_ids` strings. The new SPA hook `useRunChains` fires on every FindingList render with a run_id, so a single forensic-mode operator-initiated `?run_id=…&focus=…` link expands memory proportional to chain cardinality. Bearer-gated; degrades to DoS only after a separate auth-bypass primitive (chains with findings #2 / #6). Not novel enough to stand on its own — noted for future-deferred LIMIT/pagination work.

(e) **PR-comment deep-link** (cmd/pr_comment.rs:207-214). The new `[id]({base}/findings?run_id={run}&focus={id})` link interpolates the operator-supplied `ui_url` verbatim through `trim_url()` (no scheme allowlist, no `)` check) and concatenates URL-encoded `run_id` + `id`. The link text `id_text` is `code_safe(short_id(&row.id))`. Markdown-injection via `ui_url` containing `)` is operator-self-harm (CLI flag / config-driven); `javascript:` URLs are stripped by GitHub's CommonMark sanitiser at render time. The reflected `?focus=<finding-id>` on the SPA side flows into `params.get("focus")` → `useState` → `<FindingDetail id={selected} />` → `useFinding(id)` → `request<FindingRecord>('/findings/' + encodeURIComponent(id))`; the API gates on id existence (404 on miss), so reflected-XSS through DOM render of the id requires the id to round-trip through the API's allowlisted shape. No exploitable primitive; not emitted.

Net session-0016: validator strengthened on PATCH side, AI candidate-aggregate added, finding spec_id back-link plumbed, source-of-truth for `runs.triggered_by` straightened out. None of these add or remove finding primitives. Inventory stays at 15.

